text: Any news, @GateHub? You do realize that more than 100 hacked customers are still waiting for information from your side, don't you?

No, I'm not trolling. I thought eFin was decentralised. If it really is, then someone could create something like Gatehub for it... just like they did for the XRP Ledger DEX. The Ledger you apparently haven't studied despite being the first and oldest DEX in existence.

If you are trying to claim that they couldn't do that, then you are saying the eFin is not actually decentralised, as you are saying there is some authority that could prevent someone from creating a 3rd party wallet to interact with it.

There are no keys handed over to the DEX on the XRP Ledger itself either. But that doesn't stop someone from creating a UI or frontend of some kind to the DEX (like Gatehub) that does indeed take the keys from the user and use them to submit transactions to the DEX.
Friend asked just deleted the wallet there and keep save the private key. Is it good enough?
